node.text: "I wanted it to smell like heaven, kind of soft and cloud-like," Parton tells PEOPLE exclusively of the fragrance, which combines notes of mandarin, peony blossoms, jasmine, vanilla, sandalwood, musk, patchouli, and more. "That's why we call it Scent from Above! I thought that was a real good name for it."

node.text: A Yorkie named Macy is currently on the mend after sustaining injuries while protecting her 10-year-old owner from a coyote. 🙏 In a video of the incident, Lily Kwan is seen walking her small dog around her Toronto neighborhood when a coyote begins chasing them both injuring Macy's leg and torso. "She's a super brave dog, I love her so much," Lily Kwan, Macy's owner, said. "My dog would do anything for our family...She's our little hero." ❤️ Tap the link in bio for the full story. |📷: GoFundMe

node.text: R.I.P. 💔 Jane Withers, a legend of Hollywood's Golden Age, has died. She was 95. "My mother was such a special lady. She lit up a room with her laughter, but she especially radiated joy and thankfulness when talking about the career she so loved and how lucky she was," Withers' daughter Kendall Errair said in a statement. Tap the link in bio for more. 📷: WireImage/Getty

node.text: Jessica Alba is getting candid about having an open line of communication with her kids and going to therapy with her oldest daughter, Honor, 13. "I started going to therapy with her I think when she was 11. For me I felt like my relationship really suffered with my parents because they didn't know how to communicate with me and how I needed to be parented. So I didn't want that breakdown with Honor so we went to therapy together." Tap the link in bio for the full story. #Regram @jessicaalba

node.text: Olympic diver Jordan Windle is making his dad, who adopted him from Cambodia at 18 months old, proud at #Tokyo2020. Jerry, who is gay, had "wanted to be a dad for as long as I could remember," he has said. Jordan, who took up diving by chance at a summer camp when he was 7 years old and who went on to be the youngest diver to make it to the Olympic trials is now, at 22, competing for Team USA. "I tell everyone, when they ask me why I dive, I dive purely for my dad and how much he loves watching me," Jordan said. "Without him making all the sacrifices that he has, and his love and support the whole time we've been together, I really wouldn't be where I am today." ❤️ Tap the link in bio for the beautiful full story. #Regram @jordanpiseywindle

node.text: Allyson Felix is capping off her fifth and final games as the most decorated Olympic track athlete, man or woman, in U.S. history. 🙌 On Saturday, the 15th day of the Tokyo Games, Felix, 35, won gold in the final race of her career with relay teammates Sydney McLaughlin, Dalilah Muhammad and Athing Mu. "I have so much respect and admiration and I know I would not have been here without those who paved the way," the mom of one said. "I am grateful for my own journey, I love the sport and it is very special to be 35 and still doing what I love." ❤️ |📷: David Ramos/Getty
